results.lead_paragraph: AS a coastal island invites adventure upon the sea, so does the moon beckon the astronaut. Barren, airless, rugged, it has attractions none the less. Astronomers, and spaceminded rocketeers, have long seen the earth-moon system as a "double planet," unique in the solar system and most providentially arranged to bear a space-faring people.
